{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures","doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing","doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file for a cache monitor."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile\/init(cachemonitorname:numberofmembers:cache:)"]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"?("},{"text":"cacheMonitorName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfMembers","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cache","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Entity","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing6EntityV"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"init","extendedModule":"VHDLParsing","title":"init(cacheMonitorName:numberOfMembers:cache:)","roleHeading":"Initializer","modules":[{"name":"VHDLMemoryStructures","relatedModules":["VHDLParsing"]}],"externalID":"s:11VHDLParsing8VHDLFileV20VHDLMemoryStructuresE16cacheMonitorName15numberOfMembers0E0ACSgAA08VariableG0V_SiAA6EntityVtcfc"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile\/init(cacheMonitorName:numberOfMembers:cache:)"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cacheMonitorName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"name","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfMembers","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"members","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cache","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Entity","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing6EntityV"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"name","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The name of the monitor."}]}]},{"name":"members","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The number of entities that have access to the cache."}]}]},{"name":"cache","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The cache this monitor is managing."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A cache monitor is a file that arbitrates access to a cache when multiple entities are trying to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access it simultaneously. The cache monitor adopts a round-robin schedule to determine which entity","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has access to the cache at any point in time. This schedule is not strictly enforced by the monitor","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but instead requires each entity to relinquish access to move onto the next entity. This design","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ensures a lightweight implementation that does not require a central arbiter to manage priorities and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"timeout requirements or adopt time-based scheduling windows that can create inefficient access. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"does, however, require all entites to be aware of this fact and relinquish access when not using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cache as continuous access can result in starvation for all other entities.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To request access to the cache, an entity must assert the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ready","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" signal ","type":"text"},{"code":"high","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" at the start and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"during the entire operation of the cache. The cache monitor will assert the appropriate ","type":"text"},{"code":"en","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" signal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(en0, en1, en2, etc.) to signify which entity has access to the cache at each point in time. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"value_en","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" signals are shared between all entities but only represent valid data for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specific entity when their respective ","type":"text"},{"code":"en","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"high","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing/VHDLFile":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VHDLFile","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing8VHDLFileV"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a generic decoder."}],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VHDLFile"}],"title":"VHDLFile"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing","role":"collection","title":"VHDLParsing"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing/VHDLFile/init(cacheMonitorName:numberOfMembers:cache:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile\/init(cacheMonitorName:numberOfMembers:cache:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Create a ","type":"text"},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file for a cache monitor.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cacheMonitorName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfMembers","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cache","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Entity","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing6EntityV"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile\/init(cachemonitorname:numberofmembers:cache:)","title":"init(cacheMonitorName:numberOfMembers:cache:)"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures","role":"collection","title":"VHDLMemoryStructures"}}}